        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
          <summary>How long before ecommerce marketing increases revenue?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Google Shopping and Meta catalogue ads can drive add-to-cart and checkout activity within the first 7-14 days once the feed and tracking are live. Social content and retargeting compound over 8-12 weeks. Product and category SEO plus GEO typically show ranking and AI-citation improvements within 3-6 months. Most ecommerce clients see a meaningful lift in revenue and return on ad spend within the first 60 days of a full-service campaign — provided product pages, pricing, and fulfilment are competitive enough to convert the traffic we send.</p></div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
          <summary>Should I sell on marketplaces like Shopee and Lazada or build my own DTC store?</summary>
          <div class="faq-answer"><p>Both, but with intent. Marketplaces like Shopee and Lazada give you reach and built-in trust, but you pay commission on every order, compete on price next to identical listings, and never own the customer relationship or data. A direct-to-consumer (DTC) store keeps full margin, lets you build a brand, capture email and remarketing audiences, and drive repeat purchases. We typically use marketplaces for discovery and volume while building owned channels — SEO, email, social, and a branded store — so your highest-margin, highest-loyalty revenue isn't dependent on a platform that can change its rules overnight.</p></div>
